title: Complete coverage: Salisbury rallies for playoff-caliber football win over Northern Lehigh
text:
Complete Box Score Â» 
Salisbury made its first win over Northern Lehigh since 2006, a back-and-forth donnybrook that ended 39-29 in favor of the Falcons, one that every member of the large Homecoming crowd on hand at Salisbury will remember for a long time. 
The Falcons (4-3) rode an opportunistic defense, terrific special teams (four touchbacks on kickoffs and a 37-yard field goal, all by senior Mason Donaldson , highlighted the effort) and three long runs by Devin Irwin to defeat the Bulldogs (4-3) for just the third time in school history. Salisbury's Mason Donaldson kicked up a storm Friday night. (Jim Middlekauff | lehighvalleylive.com contributor)
